2026-02-21 15:12:19 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [{"type": "function", "function": {"name": "tavily_tool", "description": " Tavily tool to search on web  related to the hotel, destination, activities, and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "google_map_tool", "description": " Google Map tool to get distance and duration between source and destination.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"source": {"description": "source", "title": "Source", "type": "string"}, "destination": {"description": "destination", "title": "Destination", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["source", "destination"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "serper_tool", "description": " Serper tool to search on web  related to the hotel availability and other travel-related information.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"query": {"description": "query", "title": "Query", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["query"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "Validate itinerary using google_map_tool (distances/times), tavily_tool (attractions/hours), serper_tool (hotels/prices). Check if realistic. Say \"APPROVE\" if valid, else suggest fixes.", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Planner", "content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 (\u2248\u202f$600)  \n\nBelow is a ready\u2011to\u2011use itinerary that fits three comfort levels \u2013 **Budget**, **Mid\u2011range** and **Luxury** \u2013 while staying under the overall cap of \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000.  \nAll prices are **per person** (single occupancy) and shown in Indian Rupees (\u20b9).  \n\n---\n\n## 1\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK OVERVIEW  \n\n| Day | Main Theme | Key Spots | Approx. Travel Time |\n|-----|------------|-----------|---------------------|\n| **Day\u202f1** | North\u2011Goa beach & culture | Calangute \u2192 Baga \u2192 Fort Aguada \u2192 Candolim \u2192 Sunset at Chapora | 30\u201145\u202fmin between stops |\n| **Day\u202f2** | South\u2011Goa relaxation & nature | Palolem \u2192 Agonda \u2192 Cabo de Rama Fort \u2192 Return to hotel | 1\u20111.5\u202fh between stops |\n\n*All attractions are open daily; most are free or have a small entry fee (\u20b9\u202f20\u2011\u20b9\u202f250).*\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### Day\u202f1 \u2013 North Goa Vibes  \n\n| Time | Activity | Details / Tips |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **08:00** | **Breakfast** | Hotel buffet (incl. in stay) or local caf\u00e9 \u2013 try Goan *p\u00e3o* with butter & coffee. |\n| **09:00** | **Calangute Beach** | Walk the promenade, rent a **jet\u2011ski** (\u20b9\u202f800\u202f/\u202f30\u202fmin) or just relax. |\n| **11:00** | **Baga & Anjuna Market** | Souvenirs, beachwear, street\u2011food (prawn balch\u00e3o). |\n| **13:00** | **Lunch** | Beach shack \u2013 **Goan fish thali** (\u20b9\u202f250\u2011\u20b9\u202f350). |\n| **14:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Entry free; small parking fee (\u20b9\u202f30). Great photo spot. |\n| **16:00** | **Candolim Beach** | Sunset stroll; optional **parasailing** (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200). |\n| **18:30** | **Dinner** | **Fisherman\u2019s Wharf** (mid\u2011range) \u2013 Goan prawn curry, rice (\u20b9\u202f600\u2011\u20b9\u202f800). |\n| **20:30** | **Nightlife** (optional) | **Tito\u2019s** or **Mambo\u2019s** \u2013 drinks \u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f500 each. |\n| **22:30** | Return to hotel \u2013 rest. |  |\n\n---\n\n### Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Serenity  \n\n| Time | Activity | Details / Tips |\n|------|----------|----------------|\n| **07:30** | **Early Breakfast** | Hotel or quick bite (idli\u2011vada, \u20b9\u202f150). |\n| **08:30** | **Drive to Palolem** | 1\u202fh\u202f30\u202fmin via NH66. Scenic coastal road. |\n| **10:30** | **Palolem Beach** | Kayak in the lagoon (\u20b9\u202f400\u202f/\u202fhour) or just sunbathe. |\n| **12:30** | **Lunch** | Beachside shack \u2013 **Goan chicken xacuti** (\u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f400). |\n| **14:00** | **Agonda Beach** | Quiet spot; optional **turtle\u2011watching** (seasonal, free). |\n| **16:00** | **Cabo de Rama Fort** | Entry \u20b9\u202f20; panoramic sea view. |\n| **18:00** | **Sunset at Colva / Benaulim** | Quick stop for photo\u2011ops. |\n| **19:30** | **Dinner** | **Martin\u2019s Corner** (mid\u2011range) \u2013 seafood platter (\u20b9\u202f800\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f000). |\n| **21:30** | Return to hotel (or head to airport/railway station). |  |\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 ACCOMMODATION OPTIONS  \n\n| Category | Hotel (example) | Location | Avg. Nightly Rate (incl. taxes) | Amenities |\n|----------|----------------|----------|--------------------------------|-----------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Guesthouse** | Calangute | **\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200** (double\u2011room, 1\u2011bed) | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop, shared bathroom |\n| **Mid\u2011range** | **The Flora Residency** | Candolim | **\u20b9\u202f3\u202f500** (deluxe, king\u2011bed) | Pool, breakfast, sea view, air\u2011cond |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** | Benaulim (South Goa) | **\u20b9\u202f12\u202f500** (deluxe sea\u2011view) | 5\u2011star service, private beach, spa, all\u2011meals |\n\n*Rates are for **one night**; total for 2 nights = 2\u202f\u00d7\u202frate. Prices are current (Oct\u202f2024) and may vary slightly with season.*\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 TRANSPORT  \n\n| Mode | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|-------------------|-------|\n| **Round\u2011trip flight** (e.g., Mumbai\u2011Goa) | \u20b9\u202f4\u202f000\u2011\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000 (low\u2011cost carrier) | Book 2\u20113\u202fweeks ahead for best fare. |\n| **Train** (e.g., Mumbai\u202f\u2192\u202fMadgaon) | \u20b9\u202f800\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 (2nd\u202fAC) | Overnight, saves a night\u2019s hotel. |\n| **Local transport** | **Scooter rental** \u2013 \u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday (incl. fuel) <br>**Taxi/auto** \u2013 \u20b9\u202f200\u2011\u20b9\u202f400 per short ride | Most travelers prefer a scooter for flexibility. |\n| **Airport\u2011to\u2011hotel transfer** | \u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f500 (pre\u2011booked taxi) | Or use the scooter if you\u2019re comfortable. |\n\n*Choose the travel\u2011to\u2011Goa option that fits your overall budget; the figures below assume you **arrive by train** (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f000) to keep the total under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000.*\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 BUDGET BREAKDOWN  \n\n| Item | Budget (\u20b9) | Mid\u2011range (\u20b9) | Luxury (\u20b9) |\n|------|------------|--------------|------------|\n| **Transport to Goa** (train + airport\u2011taxi) | 1\u202f000 | 1\u202f000 | 1\u202f000 |\n| **Local transport** (scooter 2\u202fdays) | 700 | 700 | 700 |\n| **Accommodation** (2\u202fnights) | 2\u202f400 | 7\u202f000 | 25\u202f000 |\n| **Food** (breakfast\u2011lunch\u2011dinner, 2\u202fdays) | 2\u202f200 | 3\u202f500 | 6\u202f500 |\n| **Attractions & activities** (jet\u2011ski, parasailing, kayak, entry fees) | 2\u202f500 | 3\u202f500 | 5\u202f000 |\n| **Nightlife / drinks** (optional) | 1\u202f000 | 1\u202f500 | 2\u202f500 |\n| **Misc. (souvenirs, tips, emergency) ** | 1\u202f200 | 1\u202f200 | 1\u202f200 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f11\u202f000** | **\u20b9\u202f22\u202f400** | **\u20b9\u202f46\u202f900** |\n\nAll three totals stay comfortably **below the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling**. You can always upgrade a line\u2011item (e.g., add a spa treatment in the luxury tier) and still have a buffer.\n\n---\n\n## 6\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK\u2011TIP CHECK\u2011LIST  \n\n| \u2714\ufe0f | Item |\n|----|------|\n| **Travel tickets** | Book train/flight 2\u20113\u202fweeks early. |\n| **Hotel reservation** | Confirm cancellation policy; request sea\u2011view if possible. |\n| **Scooter licence** | Carry a valid driving licence; wear a helmet (mandatory). |\n| **Cash & cards** | Most places accept cards, but keep \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000\u2011\u20b9\u202f3\u202f000 in cash for beach shacks & small vendors. |\n| **Sun protection** | Sunscreen SPF\u202f30+, hat, sunglasses. |\n| **Health** | Carry basic meds (painkiller, motion\u2011sickness, water\u2011purifier tablets). |\n| **Packing** | Light cottons, swimwear, flip\u2011flops, a light jacket for evenings. |\n\n---\n\n## 7\ufe0f\u20e3 SAMPLE DAILY EXPENSE (Mid\u2011range)  \n\n| Category | Amount |\n|----------|--------|\n| Hotel (2\u202fnights) | \u20b9\u202f7\u202f000 |\n| Food (\u20b9\u202f1\u202f750\u202f/\u202fday) | \u20b9\u202f3\u202f500 |\n| Scooter + fuel | \u20b9\u202f700 |\n| Activities (jet\u2011ski + kayak) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| Entry fees & sightseeing | \u20b9\u202f300 |\n| Nightlife (drinks) | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f500 |\n| Misc / souvenirs | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 |\n| **Total** | **\u20b9\u202f15\u202f400** (\u2248\u202f30\u202f% of the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 budget) |\n\nYou still have **\u20b9\u202f34\u202f600** left for upgrades, shopping, or a more comfortable travel mode.\n\n---\n\n## 8\ufe0f\u20e3 FINAL RECOMMENDATION  \n\nIf you\u2019re traveling **solo** and want the best value, the **Mid\u2011range** plan (The Flora Residency) gives you a comfortable stay, a mix of beach\u2011action and cultural sights, and still leaves a healthy cash cushion for extra experiences (spa, fine\u2011dining, or a day\u2011trip to **Dudhsagar Falls**).  \n\nIf you\u2019re traveling **as a couple** and want to splurge a little, the **Luxury** option at Taj Exotica turns the two nights into a mini\u2011resort escape while still keeping the overall spend under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000.\n\nEnjoy your Goa adventure! \ud83c\udf34\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f Feel free to ask for any tweaks (e.g., vegetarian food spots, alternative activities, or a 3\u2011day extension)."}, {"role": "assistant", "tool_calls": [{"id": "fc_a6c46bd8-0454-429d-b999-173ce4ac1365", "function": {"arguments": "{\"destination\":\"Baga Beach, Goa\",\"source\":\"Calangute Beach, Goa\"}", "name": "google_map_tool"}, "type": "function"}], "content": null}, {"content": "Error occured in python script name [C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py] line number [13] error message [HolidayAgentException.__init__() missing 1 required positional argument: 'error_detail']", "role": "tool", "tool_call_id": "fc_a6c46bd8-0454-429d-b999-173ce4ac1365"}, {"role": "user", "name": "Travel_Planner", "content": "I\u2019m sorry you ran into that error. The traceback tells us that the `HolidayAgentException` class is being instantiated without the required `error_detail` argument on line\u202f13 of **GoogleMap.py**. Here\u2019s a quick checklist to get it fixed:\n\n| Step | What to Do | Why It Helps |\n|------|------------|--------------|\n| **1\ufe0f\u20e3 Open the file** | Locate `C:\\AI_2026\\Projects\\1_TravelBot\\HolidayAgent\\Tools\\GoogleMap.py` and go to line\u202f13. | You need to see the exact code that raises the exception. |\n| **2\ufe0f\u20e3 Check the exception definition** | Find the class `HolidayAgentException` (probably in a common `exceptions.py` file). It should look something like: <br>`class HolidayAgentException(Exception):`<br>`def __init__(self, error_message, error_detail):` | The constructor expects **two** positional arguments (`error_message` and `error_detail`). |\n| **3\ufe0f\u20e3 Fix the raise statement** | Change the line that raises the exception from something like: <br>`raise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API error\")` <br>to: <br>`raise HolidayAgentException(\"Google Maps API error\", str(e))` (or any relevant detail). | Supplying the missing `error_detail` satisfies the constructor signature. |\n| **4\ufe0f\u20e3 Optional \u2013 add a default** | If you want the exception to be usable with a single argument, modify the class definition: <br>`def __init__(self, error_message, error_detail=None):` <br>`self.error_detail = error_detail` | This makes `error_detail` optional, preventing similar crashes elsewhere. |\n| **5\ufe0f\u20e3 Re\u2011run the script** | After saving the change, execute the tool again. | Verify that the error is gone and that the Google Maps lookup works. |\n| **6\ufe0f\u20e3 Log the full traceback** | If the error persists, capture the full stack trace (including the original exception `e`). | It helps pinpoint whether the problem is with the API call, network, or another part of the code. |\n\n### Common Pitfalls & Quick Fixes\n| Issue | Symptom | Fix |\n|-------|---------|-----|\n| **Missing import** | `NameError: name 'HolidayAgentException' is not defined` | Ensure `from .exceptions import HolidayAgentException` (or the correct path) is at the top of the file. |\n| **Incorrect inheritance** | Exception doesn\u2019t behave like a normal error | Make sure `HolidayAgentException` inherits from `Exception` (or a subclass). |\n| **API key not set** | The code reaches the raise block because the Google Maps request fails. | Verify that the environment variable / config entry for the Google Maps API key is present and valid. |\n| **Network timeout** | `requests.exceptions.Timeout` is caught and re\u2011raised without detail. | Pass the original exception message as `error_detail` when raising. |\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```python\n# exceptions.py\nclass HolidayAgentException(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, error_message: str, error_detail: str | None = None):\n        super().__init__(error_message)\n        self.error_message = error_message\n        self.error_detail = error_detail\n\n# GoogleMap.py (relevant snippet)\nimport requests\nfrom .exceptions import HolidayAgentException\n\ndef get_place_details(place_id: str):\n    try:\n        resp = requests.get(\"https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/place/details/json\",\n                            params={\"place_id\": place_id, \"key\": API_KEY},\n                            timeout=10)\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return resp.json()\n    except Exception as e:\n        # Provide both a friendly message and the low\u2011level detail\n        raise HolidayAgentException(\n            \"Failed to fetch place details from Google Maps\",\n            str(e)\n        )\n```\n\nWith the above pattern, the exception will always receive the required `error_detail`, eliminating the `missing 1 required positional argument` error.\n\n---\n\n### Next Steps for You\n1. **Apply the fix** (add the missing argument or make it optional).  \n2. **Run a quick unit test**: call the function with a known good `place_id` to confirm it returns data without raising.  \n3. **If the error persists**, share the updated traceback (including the line that raises the exception) and I can help you dig deeper.\n\nLet me know how it goes or if you hit any other roadblocks!"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-8a1b51d7-60ec-4b9d-8a16-decda8470491", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": null, "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "fc_bb246dc9-13ca-42a2-977f-23724070bb3f", "function": {"arguments": "{\"destination\":\"Baga Beach, Goa\",\"source\":\"Calangute Beach, Goa\"}", "name": "google_map_tool"}, "type": "function"}], "reasoning": "We need to validate itinerary using tools. The user wants itinerary validation. We need to use google_map_tool for distances/times, tavily_tool for attractions/hours, serper_tool for hotels/prices. Then decide if realistic. Provide APPROVE or suggest fixes.\n\nWe have itinerary from earlier assistant. Need to check distance